        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 21 at 2:45AM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 245 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Redwater, or 12 miles northwest of Atlanta, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Wake Village, Nash, Redwater, Maud, Fouke, Genoa, Mount
Pleasant, Douglassville, Domino and Pleasant Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
